Model Summary

Fit across folds by factor model

Count of folds out of 2 with flagged problems

Notes:
mode structure is the number of folds the EFA identified the mode (most common) structure. This structure was then used in the CFA. mode structure will be 2 when the same structure was identified in every fold and < 2 when multiple factor structures were identified. The value in mode structure is the maximum value for all remaining columns. See Appendix for all structures.
improper solution is the number of folds with non-convergence or a non-positive definite matrix.
high factor correlation threshold set to 0.9.
low scale reliability threshold set to 0.6 with \(\omega_h\).
low loading threshold set to 0.3.
blanks = not applicable
